items.description: A physics-informed, data-driven framework integrating Silvaco ATLAS TCAD simulations with advanced machine learning models for fast and accurate prediction of Double-Gate Tunnel FET (DG-TFET) electrical characteristics.

items.description: Open-source framework for monitoring woody plant encroachment using Sentinel-2, spectral indices, and machine learning (RF & XGBoost)

items.name: ren.ai.v1_whitepaper-
items.description: This repository contains the white paper for ren.ai v1, an interpretable machine-learning framework for chronic kidney disease (CKD) risk stratification using routinely available clinical laboratory data.

items.name: geopolymer-ml-prediction
items.description: This repository contains all the necessary supplimentary data of our research work: "Toward a Glass-Box Framework: Interpretable and Statistically Validated Machine Learning for Geopolymer Concrete Strength Prediction"

items.name: Hybrid-ml-market-framework
items.description: A generalized hybrid machine learning and optimization framework for market return prediction under risk constraints.

items.name: BVA-SAT-FRAMEWORK
items.description: Behavioral Vulnerability Assessment Framework for IoT-Based Satellite Systems Using Machine Learning

items.name: BrainwaveAi
items.description: BrainwaveAI is an artificial intelligence project focused on building intelligent systems that learn from data and adapt over time. It provides a clean, modular framework for experimenting with machine learning and deep learning models, making it suitable for learning, research, and real-world AI applications.

items.name: adaptive-qml-drug-discovery
items.description: This project presents an adaptive hybrid quantumclassical machine learning framework for drug discovery that dynamically invokes quantum circuits based on prediction uncertainty. By selectively applying shallow or deep quantum computation only when needed, the system reduces quantum resource usage while enabling efficient decision-making.

items.name: Portfolio-Optimization-with-AI
items.description: A comprehensive portfolio optimization framework implementing multiple optimization techniques including genetic algorithms, mean-variance optimization, risk parity, and machine learning approaches.

items.name: PII-Detection-and-Anonymization
items.description: A robust framework for Detecting and Anonymizing Personally Identifiable Information (PII) in Financial Documents using hybrid rule-based Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing based techniques.

items.name: Career-Recommendation-System
items.description: Developed a machine learning-based resume parser with 86% accuracy, utilizing spaCy, Named Entity Recognition (NER) and BERT framework to extract resume information, and designed a user-friendly web interface.

items.name: ciscoNAF
items.description: A network automation framework for Cisco iOS device splitting and monitoring with an integrated machine learning algorithm

items.name: Classifying-Spam-SMS-Using-a-Hybrid-Machine-Learning-Framework
items.description: The SMS Spam Collection is a public dataset of 5,574 labeled SMS messages for spam research. It has text and multivariate features, falls under computer science, and supports classification/clustering tasks.

items.name: sentinelcam
items.description: A computer vision and machine learning pipeline on a distributed framework. Designed for an embedded network on low voltage IoT hardware.

items.name: hands-on-from-scratch
items.description: From-scratch implementations of core concepts in machine learning, math, and programming. No frameworks unless necessary  just fundamentals, step by step.

items.name: petastorm
items.description: Petastorm library enables single machine or distributed training and evaluation of deep learning models from datasets in Apache Parquet format. It supports ML frameworks such as Tensorflow, Pytorch, and PySpark and can be used from pure Python code.

items.name: Foam-Agent
items.description: Foam-Agent: An end-to-end, composable multi-agent framework for automating CFD simulations in OpenFOAM. NeurIPS 2025 Machine Learning and the Physical Sciences Workshop.

items.name: ai-fake-news-detection-xai
items.description: This repository contains an AI-driven fake news detection project using multiple machine learning models across three datasets (CIC Truth Seeker, MC_Fake, and WELFake). The project follows the KDD framework and applies explainable AI techniques (LIME and SHAP) to improve transparency and interpretability of model predictions.

items.name: trace-synthesizer
items.description: A research framework for collecting, analyzing, and eventually synthesizing execution traces using machine learning.

items.name: MetaAI-Audit-System
items.description: An end-to-end Responsible AI framework for auditing machine learning models for bias, fairness violations, ethical risk, explainability, and data leakage using industry-standard metrics.

items.description: Reinforcement-Machine learningbased optimization framework autonomously generates intermediate video frames by modeling latent motion trajectories.

items.name: synthetic-polymer-composites-dataset
items.description: The dataset was generated using a Monte Carlo framework with empirically inspired nonlinear relationships and stochastic noise. Each sample includes six input features and four output targets and is intended for supervised machine-learning regression, including multi-output random forest models for simult. prediction of polym. compos. properties.

items.name: AI-ML-with-python
items.description: This repository contains a collection of Python programs and Jupyter notebooks focusing on Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) algorithms. It covers implementations, experiments, and hands-on code examples using popular libraries and frameworks in Python.

items.name: fraud-detection-
items.description: A machine learning-based system for detecting fraudulent financial transactions. This project analyzes transaction patterns, builds predictive models, and identifies anomalies with high accuracy while minimizing false positives, providing a research-driven framework for financial fraud detection

items.name: Sake
items.description: A modular machine learning framework for budget execution & data analysis built in Python with Scikit, XGBoost, PyTorch, and TensorFlow.

items.name: EmpiricML
items.description: Python framework for building robust tabular machine learning model faster and easier.

items.name: theory-constrained-mental-health-ml
items.description: A reproducible research framework for modeling mental-health symptom severity using interpretable, theory-constrained machine learning. Uses monotonic inequality constraints on PHQ-9, GAD-7, and PCL-5 items, with stability analysis, robustness tests, psychometric checks, and full experiment tracking. Non-clinical, methods-focused.

items.name: PhiFlow
items.description: A differentiable PDE solving framework for machine learning

items.name: simple-neural-network
items.description: A neural network that analyzes a toy data set of heights and weights, mapping them to genders. This was done without the help of machine learning frameworks to deeply understand how a neural network learns.

items.name: Machine-Learning-WebApp
items.description: Trying to experiemnt more machine learning concept via Python's extensive library and framework, while building a fully functionable and interactive web app filled with these ML concept

items.name: PhishNet
items.description: A Java-based Object-Oriented Programming project that implements the Naive Bayes classifier from scratch to detect phishing emails. The project emphasizes clean class design, encapsulation, modularity, and algorithmic clarity while avoiding third-party machine learning frameworks.

items.name: ML-belajar-liniear-regression

items.description: This repository contains educational materials and code examples for learning TensorFlow, a popular open-source machine learning framework developed by Google. It provides hands-on examples covering fundamental machine learning concepts, TensorFlow basics, and core learning algorithms.

items.name: Machine_Learning_and_Cryptosystem_techniques
items.description: design and develop a robust, efficient, and scalable hybrid security framework that integrates Machine Learning (ML) and Cryptosystem techniques to protect cloud-stored data from various security threats, ensuring confidentiality, integrity, and availability

items.name: AI_Human_Text_Detection
items.description: AI vs. Human Text Detection Framework A machine learning benchmarking system designed to distinguish between AI-generated and human-written text in Bengali and English. It utilizes novel graph-based feature extraction, rigorous statistical validation, and multi-model benchmarking against state-of-the-art baselines like DetectGPT and Grover.

items.name: mlsys-cs294r-labs
items.description: Implementation of the TinyTorch ML framework and lab exercises from Harvard's CS249r Machine Learning Systems course

items.name: A-Machine-Vision-Based-System-for-Cognitive-Bias-Detection-in-Decision-Making
items.description: Proposed an automated framework combining machine vision and machine learning to assess cognitive biases in decision-making. Eye-tracking, facial expressions, and behavioral data were used to model risk tendencies. Results revealed distinct bias patterns across risk groups, supporting data-driven decision analysis.

items.name: covid19-unsupervised-triage
items.description: A dual-layer unsupervised machine learning framework (K-Means + DBSCAN) for stratifying COVID-19 mortality risk and discovering latent clinical phenotypes using static admission data.

This team of specialized AI agents collaborates to automate the entire Data Science pipelinefrom raw data loading and exploratory data analysis (EDA) to automated machine learning (ML) modeling and visualization.

items.name: RTL-Timing-Prediction-Machine-Learning-Framework-for-VLSI-Design-Automation
items.description: A machine learning framework to predict VLSI circuit delays from RTL metrics. Using 20 designs and ensemble techniques, it achieved 3.28% MAPEfar better than the 10% target. The system integrates multiple models, Bayesian optimization, SHAP explainability, delivers a production API with 12ms latency and 90% confidence intervals.

items.name: genome_classefication_project
items.description: machine Learning-Based Framework for Classifying SARS-CoV-2 Mutations by Recurrence Frequency

items.name: An-Interactive-Data-Cleaning-and-Incremental-Learning-Framework-for-Continuous-Dataset-Enhancement
items.description: This repository presents an interactive data preprocessing and incremental learning framework for structured datasets. The system automates essential data cleaning operations, including missing value handling, outlier capping, duplicate removal, feature encoding, and scaling to prepare data for machine learning tasks.

items.name: blankningsregister_project
items.description: Machinelearning driven short-selling and portfolio backtesting framework for OMXS30, with an interactive Dash dashboard.

items.name: Intelligent-House-Price-Prediction
items.description: An intelligent data collection and preprocessing framework for predicting house prices using machine learning techniques.

items.name: News_Anomaly_Detection
items.description: A Python-based framework for detecting anomalies in textual data using NLP, machine learning, and deep learning. Implements unsupervised and supervised models, transformer-based embeddings (BERT, RoBERTa), and geospatial analysis to enable automated content verification, trend monitoring, and location-based anomaly detection.

items.name: Predicting-Bitcoin-Prices-with-ARIMA-A-Machine-Learning-Approach
items.description: his repository contains a research project focused on forecasting Bitcoin (BTCUSD) prices using the ARIMA (AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average) model within a machine learning framework. The project explores the challenges of cryptocurrency volatility and demonstrates how ARIMA can be applied to timeseries data for financial forecasting.

items.name: short-horizon-stock-movement-demo
items.description: This demonstration of short-term stock price prediction aims to provide a clear predictive model within a machine learning framework.

items.name: STAR-XPLAIN
items.description: STAR-XPLAIN is an Explainable AI framework for interpretable analysis of astronomical light curves, combining classical machine learning, deep learning, and XAI methods to connect model predictions with physical astrophysical features.

items.name: ApraPipes
items.description: A pipeline framework for developing video and image processing application. Supports multiple GPUs and Machine Learning tooklits

items.name: unified-phishing-detection
items.description: A machine learning framework for detecting phishing attacks across Email, SMS, and malicious URLs using a unified Random Forest classifier and signal-preserving NLP.

items.name: CardioLab
items.description: This is the official repository for CardioLab. A machine and deep learning framework for the estimation and monitoring of laboratory abnormalities throught ECG data.
